getMaxBatchSize() - Method in class com.programmerdan.minecraft.civspy.Config
What is the upper limit per-batch in terms of records? Recommended 100, which is default.
getMaxBatchWait() - Method in class com.programmerdan.minecraft.civspy.Config
What is the max time for a batch worker to sit around waiting for enough data to reach the max_batch_size? Recommended 1000l, which is default; Note: this assumes that connection timeout is longer then 1 second! If connection timeout is shorter then one second, do not forget to make this shorter then connection timeout.
getMaxBatchWorkers() - Method in class com.programmerdan.minecraft.civspy.Config
What is the most number of batch workers that can be employed? This should tie to # of connections available in the pool; don't allow more workers then you've allowed connections.
getPeriodDelayCount() - Method in class com.programmerdan.minecraft.civspy.Config
How many aggregation periods in the past do we hold on to, before we call it "done" and commit it to the database.
getPeriodFutureCount() - Method in class com.programmerdan.minecraft.civspy.Config
How many aggregation periods into the future do we pre-create? Recommend at least a few; this is to adjust for issues where the task to commit outgoing aggregation buckets falls behind, so that "current" (future from the perspective of the "stuck" queue) data isn't lost.
